This paper deals with privacy-preserving multi-agent planning, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for solving planning problems while maintaining privacy. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the privacy guarantees of the algorithms used, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of algorithms and data structures for solving planning problems is also discussed, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithms used, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the cooperative nature of multi-agent planning, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
